Frequently
asked questions
faq.subtitle: Getting started with Reloadng
faq.content: If you’re new to reloadng, this guide will help you learn more about the platform and its features.

items.title: What is Reloadng?
items.content: Reloadng is a platform that allows customers to conveniently make payment for their day to day services like TV subscription (DStv, GOtv, StarTimes), airtime, data, Electricity (IKEDC, AEDC, EKEDC, JEDC, PHEDC, KEDC, IBEDC), WAEC and JAMB. Signing up is quick, navigating is easy and you can get started right now by creating an account using just your email and phone number or by just making payment for a service.

items.title: Must I Create An Account Before I Can Pay For A Service?
items.content: Registration is optional. All you need is your email address, phone number and a valid debit card to make payment.

items.title: What Device Can Access Reloadng?
items.subtitle: Creating an account takes only a few minutes. Here you go
items.content: Reloadng works perfectly on every device. You can access the Reloadng website through your computers, smart phones and tablets, simply log on to Reloadng For android users who want to download the Reloadng, go to Google Play Store to download the app or simply Click here to Sign up.

items.title: How To Create An Account
items.subtitle: Creating an account takes only a few minutes. Here you go
items.content2: - Click on register at the top of the webpage.
items.content3: - Enter your email address, phone number and a password you can easily remember. Then click on sign up.

items.title: How Do I Pay For A Service?
items.content: You can make payments using either; Debit card, or Wallet payment (This is available for registered users only).

items.title: My Transaction Failed But I Was Debited
items.content: Please ensure you contact our 24-hour support team by chatting us on our Live-chat platform or dialing 08035001523 or by sending a mail to support@reload.ng immediately you experience this. Usually you should get an auto-reversal of the payment from your bank within 24 hours

items.title: I Purchased Token Using a Wrong Meter Number, Can It Be Transferred?
items.content: No, it cannot. Token is generated and encrypted using the meter number used. This means that token once generated can only be used by the specific meter. A transfer is impossible.

items.title: What Are The Card Options Available For Payment?
items.content: You can pay with your MasterCard, Visa card and Verve card.
